    <div class="first-container">
        <img class="container-img" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.thecrimson.com/photos/2004/03/18/123540_1195502.jpg" alt="" srcset="">
        <p class="desc-box">NoteRoom was developed as a collaborative effort between Anirban Biswas, Devajit Mutsuddy, and Moshiur Rahman, with each member bringing unique expertise to the project. Anirban, who initiated the idea, played a dual role in project direction and frontend development, guiding the team toward achieving its goals while ensuring the user interface was visually appealing and functional. Devajit focused on UI/UX design, crafting an intuitive interface and developing wireframes using Figma to visually map out the user journey. Moshiur, the backend developer, built the platform's infrastructure, ensuring seamless data management and integration with college websites.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="second-container">
        <img class="container-img" src="https://static.independent.co.uk/s3fs-public/thumbnails/image/2016/09/19/17/mark-zuckerberg.jpg" alt="" srcset="">
        <div class="info-box">
        <h3 class="desc-title">
            Project Direction and Frontend Development – Led by Anirban Biswas
        </h3>
        <p class="desc-box-2">
            Anirban played a crucial role in both the direction of the project and the frontend development. As the project director, he ensured that the team remained focused on achieving key milestones, kept the development process on track, and facilitated collaboration between departments. In the frontend development, Anirban worked on building the platform’s interface, focusing on a mobile-first design to optimize user experience across devices. His responsibilities included implementing the visual and interactive aspects of the platform, ensuring the user interface was functional and easy to navigate.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="third-container">
        <img class="container-img" src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/iIES3qXicDqQ/v0/-1x-1.webp" alt="" srcset="">
        <div class="info-box">
        <h3 class="desc-title">
            Backend Development – Led by Moshiur Rahman
        </h3>
        <p class="desc-box-2">
            
Moshiur was responsible for the backend development, handling the server-side functionality that powers the platform. His role included managing the databases, developing APIs, and ensuring that NoteRoom’s infrastructure could handle user activity efficiently and securely. Moshiur worked on integrating the platform with college systems, enabling seamless data flow between the platform and external systems. His focus was on creating a scalable, stable backend that ensured NoteRoom's performance was reliable, even with increasing user loads.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="fourth-container">
